marc_liberation.title: Alma implementation for barcode#scsb
Alma implementation for patron#patron_info

comments.body: You can't get an API response at all if there are no active barcodes. We're not sure why some people have barcodes that aren't active. But we aren't going to worry about this.
There's a user identifier type table in alma if you search for "user identifier types"

Outstanding data needs (@pmgreen will pursue these):
* Need netids in the records
* Need an entry in the user identifier types table tied to netids.

In the meantime we can work on this issue by obtaining fixtures using `user_id_type=BARCODE` with a barcode and/or `user_id_type=all_unique` with an institution id, then mocking them as responses to a request with `user_id_type=NET_ID`.

NetIDs are currently in Alma as `user_title` (having migrated from `PATRON.TITLE`). To get netids into Alma as `NET_ID`, we need to run an SIS integration profile job, after data has been checked. Fulfillment staff are doing the methodical checks of patron records. If no issues have been found, ExL suggests that we could begin testing netids by adding some manually (identifiers tab in patron records).
